criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Age and gender: 18-75 years old, male and female unlimited;

          2. Patients with NSCLC who are eligible for video-assisted upper left/upper right
             lobectomy;

          3. Participants volunteer to participate the study and signed the informed consent form;

          4. Preoperative pulmonary function test: FEV1> 1L and FEV1> 60% of predicted value;

          5. Preoperative ECOG:0-1;

          6. Preoperative ASA:I-II.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Women in the the period of pregnancy or lactation;

          2. Patients suffering from any serious mental illness;

          3. Having the history of any thoracic surgery (only including intrathoracic surgery,
             excluding any superficial surgery like breast surgery, etc.);

          4. Patients with unstable angina pectoris or myocardial infarction within half a year;

          5. Patients with cerebral infarction or cerebral hemorrhage within half a year;

          6. Received continuous systemic glucocorticoid therapy in the past 1 month;

          7. Abnormal coagulation function, bleeding tendency or receiving thrombolytic or
             antiplatelet treatment recently;

          8. Patients requiring emergency operation for severe lung cancer
             complication(bleeding/pneumothorax);

          9. Patients with severe hepatic,renal insufficiency or other systematic dysfunction;

         10. Other conditions that are not suitable for the surgery.
